And that is what it is about, using the letters of our genome, rewriting the letters of the first and last name of those who lost their identity.
How do we do it?
Using genetics, comparing.
To identify is necessarily to compare.
To compare a father and a son, to find out if they are related in that relationship, I have to compare them.
